      h1 Icon Vue Component
      p Icon Vue component represents Icon element. It is ready to be used with custom icons, <a href="../icons/" target="_blank">Framework7 Icons</a>, <a href="https://material.io/icons/" target="_blank">Material Icons</a>, <a href="http://fontawesome.io/" target="_blank">Font Awesome</a>, <a href="http://ionicons.com/" target="_blank">Ionicons</a>.
      h2 Usage example
      pre
        code
          | &lt;!-- Default back icon --&gt;
          | &lt;f7-icon icon="icon-back"&gt;&lt;/f7-icon&gt;
          | 
          | &lt;!-- Some custom icon --&gt;
          | &lt;f7-icon icon="icon-home"&gt;&lt;/f7-icon&gt;
          | 
          | &lt;!-- F7 Icons font icon --&gt;
          | &lt;f7-icon f7="home"&gt;&lt;/f7-icon&gt;
          | 
          | &lt;!-- Material Icons font icon --&gt;
          | &lt;f7-icon material="home"&gt;&lt;/f7-icon&gt;
          | 
          | &lt;!-- Font Awesome icons font icon --&gt;
          | &lt;f7-icon fa="home"&gt;&lt;/f7-icon&gt;
          | 
          | &lt;!-- Ionicons icons font icon --&gt;
          | &lt;f7-icon ion="home"&gt;&lt;/f7-icon&gt;
          | 
          | &lt;!-- F7 icons font icon with custom size and color --&gt;
          | &lt;f7-icon f7="home" size="44px" color="blue"&gt;&lt;/f7-icon&gt;
          | 
          | &lt;!-- Conditional icon --&gt;
          | &lt;f7-icon if-ios="f7:home" if-material="material:home"&gt;&lt;/f7-icon&gt;
      p Renders to:
      pre
        code
          | &lt;!-- Default back icon --&gt;
          | &lt;i class="icon icon-back"&gt;&lt;/i&gt;
          | 
          | &lt;!-- Some custom icon --&gt;
          | &lt;i class="icon icon-home"&gt;&lt;/i&gt;
          | 
          | &lt;!-- F7 Icons font icon --&gt;
          | &lt;i class="icon f7-icons"&gt;home&lt;/i&gt;
          | 
          | &lt;!-- Material Icons font icon --&gt;
          | &lt;i class="icon material-icons"&gt;home&lt;/i&gt;
          | 
          | &lt;!-- Font Awesome icons font icon --&gt;
          | &lt;i class="icon fa fa-home"&gt;&lt;/i&gt;
          | 
          | &lt;!-- Ionicons icons font icon --&gt;
          | &lt;f7-icon ion="home"&gt;&lt;/f7-icon&gt;
          | &lt;i class="icon ion-home"&gt;&lt;/i&gt;
          | 
          | &lt;!-- F7 icons font icon with custom size and color --&gt;
          | &lt;i class="icon f7-icons color-blue" style="font-size:44px"&gt;home&lt;/i&gt;
          | 
          | &lt;!-- Conditional icon --&gt;
          | &lt;!-- In case of iOS theme is used/active --&gt;
          | &lt;i class="icon f7-icons"&gt;home&lt;/i&gt;
          | &lt;!-- In case of Material theme is used/active --&gt;
          | &lt;i class="icon material-icons"&gt;home&lt;/i&gt;
      h2 Properties
      table.params-table
        thead
          tr
            th Prop
            th Type
            th Description
        tbody
          tr
            td color
            td string
            td Icon color. One of <a href="../docs/color-themes.html">default colors</a>
          tr
            td size
            td string/number
            td Icon size in px
          tr
            td icon
            td string
            td Custom icon class
          tr
            td f7
            td string
            td Name of F7 Icons font icon
          tr
            td material
            td string
            td Name of Material Icons font icon
          tr
            td fa
            td string
            td Name of Font Awesome font icon
          tr
            td ion
            td string
            td Name of Ionicons font icon
          tr
            td if-ios
            td string
            td Icon to be used in case of iOS theme is used. Consists of icon family and icon name divided by colon, e.g. <code>f7:home</code> or <code>ion:home</code>
          tr
            td if-material
            td string
            td Icon to be used in case of Material theme is used. Consists of icon family and icon name divided by colon, e.g. <code>material:home</code> or <code>fa:home</code>